                 <origDate when="1920" evidence="internal">20 March 1920</origDate>.
                 According to the <ref target="#coloph1">colophon</ref>,
                  the writing was completed on <date>1 Maggābit 1912 <hi rendition="simple:smallcaps">EC</hi>,
                        the year of John (= 20 March 1920 <hi rendition="simple:smallcaps">CE</hi>)</date>,
                  during the tenure of the Coptic patriarch Cyril V (<date>1874–1927</date>).
                   The manuscript was copied in Egypt by the scribe
                   <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11958WaldaM">Walda Māryām</persName>.
                  The owner or commissioner of the manuscript might be the person whose name is
                  imprinted on the spine, <foreign xml:lang="ar"> يوسف نجده الحبشي </foreign>,
                  which could be interpreted as
                  the Arabic translation of an Ethiopian name, such as
                  <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12972Yosef">Yosef ʾAggazaw (‘the Abyssinian’)</persName>.

